Package me.lokka30.levelledmobs.misc

Enum LevellableState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<LevellableState>
      • me.lokka30.levelledmobs.misc.LevellableState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<LevellableState>
    public enum LevellableState
extends java.lang.Enum<LevellableState>
    This provides information on if a mob is levellable or not, and if not, a reason is supplied. A mob is levellable if their LevellableState = ALLOW.
    Since:
    2.4.0
    Author:
    lokka30

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      ALLOWED
      The entity is ALLOWED to be levelled.
      DENIED_CONFIGURATION_BLOCKED_ENTITY_TYPE
      settings.yml has been configured to block mobs of such entity type from being levelled
      DENIED_CONFIGURATION_BLOCKED_SPAWN_REASON
      settings.yml has been configured to block mobs that spawn with a specific SpawnReason through CreatureSpawnEvent.
      DENIED_CONFIGURATION_BLOCKED_WORLD
      settings.yml has been configured to block mobs spawning in entity's world from being levelled
      DENIED_CONFIGURATION_COMPATIBILITY_CITIZENS

      settings.yml has been configured to block MythicMobs mobs from being levelled.
      DENIED_CONFIGURATION_COMPATIBILITY_SHOPKEEPERS
      settings.yml has been configured to block Shopkeepers NPCs from being levelled.
      DENIED_CONFIGURATION_COMPATIBILITY_WORLD_GUARD
      WorldGuard region flag states that mobs are not levellable in its region
      DENIED_CONFIGURATION_CONDITION_NAMETAGGED
      settings.yml has been configured to block nametagged mobs from being levelled.
      DENIED_CONFIGURATION_CONDITION_TAMED
      settings.yml has been configured to block tamed mobs from being levelled.
      DENIED_FORCE_BLOCKED_ENTITY_TYPE
      the plugin force blocked an entity type, such as a PLAYER or ARMOR STAND which are not meant to be 'levelled mobs'.
      DENIED_NO_APPLICABLE_RULES
      If no rules in the rule list applied to the mob then it will be denied
      DENIED_OTHER
      When a reason is not applicable, use this.
